description: Gets properties associated with a customized model you imported.

parameters.name: modelIdentifier
parameters.description: Name or Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the imported model.

nested_items.name: modelArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) associated with this imported model.

nested_items.name: modelName
nested_items.description: The name of the imported model.

nested_items.name: jobName
nested_items.description: Job name associated with the imported model.

nested_items.name: jobArn
nested_items.description: Job Amazon Resource Name (ARN) associated with the imported model.

nested_items.name: modelDataSource
nested_items.description: The data source for this imported model.

nested_items.name: s3DataSource
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 data source of the imported model.

nested_items.name: s3Uri
nested_items.description: The URI of the Amazon S3 data source.

nested_items.name: creationTime
nested_items.description: Creation time of the imported model.

nested_items.name: modelArchitecture
nested_items.description: The architecture of the imported model.

nested_items.name: modelKmsKeyArn
nested_items.description: The imported model is encrypted at rest using this key.

nested_items.name: instructSupported
nested_items.description: Specifies if the imported model supports converse.

nested_items.name: customModelUnits
nested_items.description: Information about the hardware utilization for a single copy of the model.

nested_items.name: customModelUnitsPerModelCopy
nested_items.description: The number of custom model units used to host a model copy.

nested_items.name: customModelUnitsVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the custom model unit. Use to determine the billing rate for the custom model unit.
